  "education": {
    "market_education": {
      "summary_en": "U.S. equities drifted slightly lower Monday, with the S&P 500 off 0.1% and the NASDAQ down 0.2%, as investors traded cautiously ahead of a heavy week of Big Tech earnings and key economic releases. The session lacked a single dominant catalyst, with traders balancing lingering trade-policy uncertainty against resilient corporate earnings so far this cycle. Energy and defensive names held up better than growth-oriented tech, suggesting mild risk-off rotation without a full flight to safety.",
